<b>Subject:</b> Geoffrey rules, he's a great guy. (nt)<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1071" TARGET=_self>I asked Verant to modify the spell resistance for PvP combat - their reply</A> (TheBlack[BCK])
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> Our concerns are being considered. There is hope for EQ PvP yet!

<BR>&gt; ---------------------------------
<P>&gt; Geoffrey,
<P>&gt; I and my friends in the PvP Community will be holding our breath
<BR>&gt; until then. I wish you
<BR>&gt; luck in getting the team to adopt changes such as this for PvP!
<BR>&gt; Even if they are nothing
<BR>&gt; more than a crude hack, such as dividing the resistance factor
<BR>&gt; in half if PvP level is within
<BR>&gt; 4, this would be a vast improvement over the current state of
<BR>&gt; affairs. We aren't asking for
<BR>&gt; perfection, just the rudiments of a workable system.
<P>&gt; Thanks again for taking our concerns to heart.
<P>&gt; The Black
<P>&gt; gzatkin@verant.com wrote:
<P>&gt; Right now, casting on anything (player or monster) higher level
<BR>&gt; than
<BR>&gt; you is harder - they save more often. I can see where it could
<BR>&gt; cause
<BR>&gt; trouble in PvP - I'll bring it up in our tuning meeting.
<P>&gt; Geoffrey C. Zatkin
<P>&gt; Arch-Magi of Norrath
<BR>&gt; ___________________________________________
<BR>&gt; ____________________________________
